{"action": "edit", "code": "def find_indexes_on_connection_line(start: Tuple[int, int], end: Tuple[int, int]) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given the starting and ending points of a diagonal line, returns a list of all the indices of the blocks that lie on the\n    connection line between the two corresponding blocks.\n\n    Args:\n    - start (Tuple[int, int]): The starting point of the diagonal line.\n    - end (Tuple[int, int]): The ending point of the diagonal line.\n\n    Returns:\n    - List[Tuple[int, int]]: A list of all the indices of the blocks that lie on the connection line between the two corresponding blocks.\n    \"\"\"\n    indexes = []\n    x1, y1 = start\n    x2, y2 = end\n    dx = abs(x2 - x1)\n    dy = abs(y2 - y1)\n    x = x1\n    y = y1\n    n = 1 + dx + dy\n    x_inc = 1 if x2 > x1 else -1\n    y_inc = 1 if y2 > y1 else -1\n    error = dx - dy\n    dx *= 2\n    dy *= 2\n    for i in range(n):\n        indexes.append((x, y))\n        if error > 0:\n            x += x_inc\n            error -= dy\n        else:\n            y += y_inc\n            error += dx\n    return indexes\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    color_list = find_non_black_colors(input_grid)\n    output_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    for color in color_list:\n        point_list = find_block_indices(input_grid, color)\n        output_grid = connect_diagonal_blocks(output_grid, point_list, color)\n    return output_grid\ndef find_block_indices(input_grid: np.ndarray, color: int) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    indices = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == color:\n                indices.append((i, j))\n    return indices\ndef connect_diagonal_blocks(input_grid: np.ndarray, point_list: List[Tuple[int, int]], color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    points = find_indexes_on_connection_line(point_list[0], point_list[1])\n    for point in points:\n        input_grid = connect_diagonal_blocks_in_grid(input_grid, point, color)\n    return input_grid\ndef find_non_black_colors(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[int]:\n    color_list = []\n    for row in input_grid:\n        for color in row:\n            if color != black and color not in color_list:\n                color_list.append(color)\n    return color_list\ndef connect_diagonal_blocks_in_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray, point_list: List[Tuple[int, int]], color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a grid, a list of points and a color, connect the diagonal blocks in the grid with the corresponding color.\n\n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): The input grid.\n    - point_list (List[Tuple[int, int]]): A list of points in the grid.\n    - color (int): The color to be used for connecting the diagonal blocks.\n\n    Returns:\n    - np.ndarray: A grid with the diagonal blocks connected with the corresponding color.\n    \"\"\"\n    points = find_indexes_on_connection_line(point_list[0], point_list[1])\n    for point in points:\n        input_grid = _hole6(input_grid, point, color)\n    return input_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    color_list = `find the list of non-black color in the grid, ignore duplicates`(input_grid)\n    output_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    for color in color_list:\n        point_list = `find the list of index of 2 blocks with the corresponding color in the grid`(input_grid, color)\n        output_grid = `connect the diagonal line between 2 blocks with the corresponding color in the grid`(output_grid, point_list, color)\n    return output_grid\n    \ndef connect_diagonal_blocks(input_grid: np.ndarray, point_list: List[Tuple[int, int]], color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    points = `find the list of indexes of blocks on the connection line between 2 corresponding blocks`(point_list[0], point_list[1])\n    for point in points:\n        input_grid = `fill the corresponding bloock in the grid with the corresponding color`(input_grid, point, color)\n    return input_grid\n    ", "gpt_code": "def find_indexes_on_connection_line(start: Tuple[int, int], end: Tuple[int, int]) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given the starting and ending points of a diagonal line, returns a list of all the indices of the blocks that lie on the\n    connection line between the two corresponding blocks.\n\n    Args:\n    - start (Tuple[int, int]): The starting point of the diagonal line.\n    - end (Tuple[int, int]): The ending point of the diagonal line.\n\n    Returns:\n    - List[Tuple[int, int]]: A list of all the indices of the blocks that lie on the connection line between the two corresponding blocks.\n    \"\"\"\n    indexes = []\n    x1, y1 = start\n    x2, y2 = end\n    dx = abs(x2 - x1)\n    dy = abs(y2 - y1)\n    x = x1\n    y = y1\n    n = 1 + dx + dy\n    x_inc = 1 if x2 > x1 else -1\n    y_inc = 1 if y2 > y1 else -1\n    error = dx - dy\n    dx *= 2\n    dy *= 2\n    for i in range(n):\n        indexes.append((x, y))\n        if error > 0:\n            x += x_inc\n            error -= dy\n        else:\n            y += y_inc\n            error += dx\n    return indexes\ndef find_block_indices(input_grid: np.ndarray, color: int) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\n    indices = []\n    for i in range(input_grid.shape[0]):\n        for j in range(input_grid.shape[1]):\n            if input_grid[i][j] == color:\n                indices.append((i, j))\n    return indices\ndef find_non_black_colors(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[int]:\n    color_list = []\n    for row in input_grid:\n        for color in row:\n            if color != black and color not in color_list:\n                color_list.append(color)\n    return color_list\ndef connect_diagonal_blocks_in_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray, point_list: List[Tuple[int, int]], color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a grid, a list of points and a color, connect the diagonal blocks in the grid with the corresponding color.\n\n    Args:\n 